EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 072300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING A LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS EXP TO BE
CENTRED OVER THE N SEA. OVERNIGHT THIS LOW IS FCST TO MOV
E ACROSS SERN SCANDINAVIA AND FILL WITH A RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE TRANSITING ACROSS THE REGION DURING FRIDAY. ON
SATURDAY THIS RIDGE SINKS SEWARDS AS A LARGE LOW PRESSURE
SYSTEM NEAR ICELAND MOVS EWARDS ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN
BASIN DURING THE WEEKEND.
GALES OR NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ARE LIKELY ON THURSDAY
EVENING IN GERMAN BIGHT HUMBER DOGGER AND FORTIES
SPREADING TO FISHER OVERNIGHT. ON FRIDAY MORNING WINDS
WILL EASE FM THE W. HOWEVER FURTHER GALES WILL SPREAD
INTO THE NW OF CULLERCOATS DURING FRIDAY EVENING WITH
SEV GALES POSS IN THE FAR NW. GALES ARE THEN EXP TO
SPREAD TO ALL PARTS FOR SATURDAY. ON SUNDAY FURTHERRGALES
ARE LIKELY IN THE NW OF THE REGION WITH STRG WINDS
ELSEWHERE.
